TITLE: MarkdownRenderer 'on' Event Listener
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to listen for the `beginPage` or `endPage` events using the `on` method of the `MarkdownRenderer`. The callback function receives a `MarkdownPageEvent` object as an argument, allowing you to modify the page rendering process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typedoc2md/typedoc-plugin-markdown/blob/main/devguide/typedoc-plugin-markdown/types/interfaces/MarkdownRenderer.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
app.renderer.on(MarkdownPageEvent.BEGIN, (renderer) => {});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configure Docusaurus with typedoc-plugin-markdown
DESCRIPTION: Configures the Docusaurus `docusaurus.config.js` file to include the `docusaurus-plugin-typedoc` plugin and its options.  The `entryPoints` and `tsconfig` options are specified to tell TypeDoc where to find the source files and TypeScript configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typedoc2md/typedoc-plugin-markdown/blob/main/docs/content/plugins/docusaurus/quick-start.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
  // Add option types
  plugins: [
    [
      'docusaurus-plugin-typedoc',

      // Options
      {
        entryPoints: ['../src/index.ts'],
        tsconfig: '../tsconfig.json',
      },
    ],
  ],
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring TypeDoc plugins
DESCRIPTION: This JSON configuration file specifies the plugins that TypeDoc should use, in this case, typedoc-plugin-markdown and typedoc-vitepress-theme. This configuration ensures that TypeDoc generates markdown output and applies the VitePress theme.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typedoc2md/typedoc-plugin-markdown/blob/main/docs/content/plugins/vitepress/quick-start.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "plugin": ["typedoc-plugin-markdown", "typedoc-vitepress-theme"]
}
```

