TITLE: Extend Theme with Custom Render Context in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to extend the theme to provide custom templates, partials, and helpers by creating a custom render context class.  It overrides the `getRenderContext` method to return an instance of `MyMarkdownThemeContext`. It then overrides the `templates`, `partials` and `helpers` properties of the context class to add custom logic.  The `...this.templates` syntax is used to inherit the default values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typedoc2md/typedoc-plugin-markdown/blob/main/packages/typedoc-plugin-markdown/internal-docs/custom-theme.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class MyMarkdownTheme extends MarkdownTheme {
  getRenderContext(page) {
    return new MyMarkdownThemeContext(this, page, this.application.options);
  }
}

class MyMarkdownThemeContext extends MarkdownThemeContext {
  // customise templates
  templates = {
    ...this.templates,
    reflection: (model) => {
      return `New template for ${model.name}!`;
    },
  };

  // customise partials
  partials = {
    ...this.partials,
    header: (model) => {
      return `\n# Welcome to custom header for ${this.page.project.name} project and ${model.name} model!\nUse my new helper - ${this.helpers.newHelper()}\n   `;
    },
  };

  // customise helpers
  helpers = {
    ...this.helpers,
    newHelper: () => {
      return 'New helper!';
    },
  };
}
```

